			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Greetings Mages, just some thoughts on the topic.<br><br>I have preferred Conjuration because chaining pets has been a very important method, and also for a Greater Balance of offensive Nukeing.<br><br>I noticed that the fire based Evocation series has the truely high mana-ratios, the AE's.  This gives a mage a lot of power in the realm of Fire based offensive spells.  But I have found versatility to be pretty important in offensive nukes.  So my specialization mastery in Conjuration drops the mana-cost of some Conjuration nukes, I hear the actual saved amount of mana is based on a die roll command.  But with many spells cast, it does average out some, so chain casting my level 57 Magic DD is worth doing now.<br><br>I am currently at the Brownie camp in Lesser faydark, and I have noticed that even without Mala series Debuff, my Magic based nukes are landing with good ratios.  I think the brownies have very nice Fire resist once they buff up.  Better magic resists after buffs too, but my best fire ratio is my AE rains. But they seem to have a higher resist ratio then strait DD's.<br><br>Chaining pets post lvl 49+ has been a powerfull strategy, especially in low aggro areas with mobs that dont regenerate health.  I remember killing Quag Maelstrom in OOT easily at 49 with earth pets using good chain methods.  I wish I had a DS robe and BO3 pants, that would make chaining pets so much better.  Around 300 mana saved per pet.  I currently hunt the Level 50 Alliwezasaurus(spelling?) in OOT using chained pets.  That mob seems to have like 12k, to 15k HP, and he triple hits for 130's pretty fast too.  Rain spells rock on him though, good success rate after Malosi.<br><br>So I can see large reasons for Mastery of Conjuration Specialization.  Mod rods, Chaining pets well, Magic nukes, even making stuff like Lev rings when I'm soloing, or for groups is nice with that Mastery.<br><br>I would love to see other's thoughts on why Evocation would be a good Mastery for 57+<br><br>/buffs Fire Resist<br> <p><B><font color=green>Eandori Raintree 57th Conjurer <br>Nitefal 29th Necromancer <br>Elvarian Raintree 27th Enchanter<br></font></B></center></p><i></i><br />_________________<br /><Center><b><a href= "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=36994">Sage Eandori Raintree</a></b>
