			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">While it's obviously true that the Evocation has the nuke power, I find myself using 57 shock of swords alot now.  The stun part of it has been huge when I'm soloing casters.  And also, when I try very hard mobs the chaining pets tactic is just amazing.  Couple that with Velious robe and pants (DS and Burnout)  And you are doing LOTS of damage for very little mana.<br><br>My best ratio single DD will be fire at 59, but bolts are not always viable.  And the bolt does not stun.  Char does seem to have a low resist rate, and it is a faster cast time.  So it's very good, but 57 shock is a better ratio with a stun.  Scars of Sigil is good, but I only really use that when I&quot;m in trouble, and I need to nuke QUICKLY.  If I'm doing things right, I'm not in that much trouble most of the time.<br><br>Now all the Fire AE Evocation spells are of course the best, but I notice that I mainly use those in raids with very special groups.  And 95% of those times, I have clarity or some other form of mana regen.  The rain's are the ones I used the most when I solo out of the AE's.  But the resist rate for rain is much higher then single target DD's.  So actually, 1 rain cast with 1-2 waves resisted ends up equaling out with 3 Shock of swords with a mastery of specialization.<br><br>For example, I'm killing brownies in Lesser faydark now.  I'm switching back and forth between Sirocco rain, and Shock of Steel for my nuke power (both after Malosini.)  I normally finish each fight with almost a whole blue bubble of mana more, when I use the 57 shock.  First of all because I don't need to Malosini, but even when I do, it still comes out ahead.<br><br>I would love it if somebody specializing in Evocation did the same test on the Brownie Guards in Lesser fay.  Just try Evocation nukes one for a few rounds, then try 57 Shock of Swords the next.  Then report your findings back here.  I gotta tell ya though, interrupting the brownie's heals with the shock is HUGE.  Save's tons of mana.<br><br>I have been soloing lvl 50's all over the place lately.  Giants Guards outside of Kael on the EW side.  And the Ali in OOT.  I notice that other mages on these pages say Ali is near undoable, but I have not failed yet.  I'm telling ya, Chaining pets with specialization in Conj. is pretty huge.<br><br>Looking forward to more reponses, thanks for the input so far!! <p><B><font color=green>Eandori Raintree 58th Conjurer <br>Nitefal 29th Necromancer <br>Elvarian Raintree 28th Enchanter<br></font></B></center></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ueandori.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eandori</A> at: 7/24/01 5:17:43 pm<br></i><br />_________________<br /><Center><b><a href= "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=36994">Sage Eandori Raintree</a></b>
