				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Just tried out something new on Ali the other day.  I cast a lvl 49 pet, and let him eat it while I ran to the other side of the island and kept pet on target.  When the pet died, I cast one more lvl 49 pet, and let him eat that too while again I medded on the other side of the island.  So when that pet died, Ali was at about 90%, and I was VERY high on aggro list.  <br><br>Now that I was high on aggro, I made a water vocerate (backstabber) and gave it BO4 and expedience, and then turned off taunt.  Then I got within range to aggro Ali again, and just kited him around while the pet got free backstabs.  He eventually turned and killed that pet, but that is great because I was even higher on the hate list, pet was not on it since it died and Ali was at about 40%.  Then I made my final water pet, BO4 and Expedience again, taunt off again, and kited him until he started running and the pet just spanked him down.<br><br>so it was 4 pets, 2 BO4's, and 2 casts of Expedience.  Took about 15-20 min to kill and low internet lag (because I was kiting)  I had Jboots to keep me ahead of him, and I have a burnt wood staff to add to the damage.<br><br>This is what I'm going to do from now on when I solo him.  I'm only planning on doing it until I get 2 more blue diamonds for some earrings.  It's not a place I would go for exp, the rate is very low.  But taking out Ali is just plain fun.  <br><br>If I had Velious robe (DS) and pants (BO3) I'm willing to bet you could just chain out lvl 49 pets or monster summons until he dies.<br><br>Just remember to start running away from him before the pet dies, so you have time to cast another.  If your pet dies before hand, you can kite enough of a lead on him to do it.  If you have Jboots you can outrun him.<br><br>NOW BACK TO THE ORIGINAL TOPIC:<br><br>After looking at all the luclin item summons for mages, I'm even more confident that Conj. is the way to go post lvl 57.  Some people say mages are COTH and mod rod whores right?  Both are conjuration based.  Pets are conj, item summons are conj, magic nukes are conj.  Yep I'm convinced now. <p><B><font color=green>Eandori Raintree 58th Conjurer <br>Nitefal 29th Necromancer <br>Elvarian Raintree 28th Enchanter<br></font></B></center></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ueandori.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eandori</A> at: 8/16/01 12:38:53 am<br></i><br />_________________<br /><Center><b><a href= "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=36994">Sage Eandori Raintree</a></b>
