			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">From lvl 20-current I had been a Conjuration specialist.  The reasoning was simple: Mod rods, Pets, SoR's, Lev Rings and Shock of Steel.  This was pre-Kunark, when our best DD was lava bolt LoS.  Back in those days, mages that went evocation were secretely laughed at.<br><br>I stuck to my guns even after Kunark and the addition of some nice mana ratio DD's, because I thought I would never get to the post-50 game before I burned out and quit.  This almost came true, my mage dinged 34 and then I started making twinks.  My new warrior dinged 52, my new cleric dinged 45 and my ranger dinged 30 before I broke out my mage again and dinged 35.<br><br>Well, about three months ago when I dinged 55 and got Sirroco, I immediately saw the huge damage/mana ratio and began to second-guess my specialization.  I decided instead of rushing things, I would do some serious research and some logging.  This is what I discovered about myself:<br><br>As it turns out, in normal grouping modes (which compromise aprox 90% of all my game-time) I chain-cast pets only upon startup to ensure I get the best pet.  During this, I use a focus item to reclaim the mana.  Once my group gets goin, I might have to kill my pet and resummon, or chain-cast once per week.<br><br>Since I'm a grouping-type of mage, I rarely summon lev rings because 95% of all my hunting is done in dungeons, where one cannot leviate, or is no need for it.  The 5% of the time I use lev rings, I'm usually traveling or farming stuff for trade skills or quests...and pharmin' mages only need enough mana to keep pet DS'd, BO'd and a couple reserve Scars.<br><br>The extreme vast majority (98%) of my groups consist of a cleric, and the other 2% is comprised either of shaman/druids, or just a caster group.  On average, during exp hunts I will experience the need to summon perhaps 10 mod rods per week.<br><br>Regarding CoH, this is a fantastic yet little used spell during the 95% of the time I play.  I CoH perhaps once per week, and that's usually summoning friends from one side of the zone to the other...because they can't travel it due to faction or something.<br><br>Now that I'm 56, I see a noticable increase in my spell resist rates - Sirroco is doing full damage on succeptable mobs 80% of the time.  Sirroco is my bread and butter due to the mana/dmg ratio.  Next in line is Scars of Sigil, which is my backup, or fast shooter for gating mobs.  Both, evocation based.<br><br>I stopped using Shock of Steel at level 55 when i got Sirroco.  Usually, if the mobs can't be hit with Sirroco, they are hard to land a lvl 44 shock on also - not to mention the worse ratio and the insignificane of doing 585dmg on a 12Khp mob.<br><br>Regarding the 5% of my time which involve raids...<br><br>I do summon a lot of pets because of pathing or aggro.  I estimate I summon 3-5 pets per hour if pets are allowed, though sometimes I'm lucky and I get a pet that minds well and will last the raid duration.  I must admit that keeping pets up are usually a low priority, I'm more concerned with keeping the MA ds'd and helping with debufs.<br><br>Mod rods are summoned a lot, but not to the point of being crucial usually.  With C2 and bard songs and necro's pumping mana, a lot of times the cleric will not want rods if there are other options available.  I summon anywhere from 0-20 rods per raid, more if there are wipeouts, fewer if rez sticks are around.<br><br>CoH usage is hugely random, depending on the puller skill and the mobs you are after.  I can count the number of times I have had to CoH a great monk puller with one finger.  I can't count the number of times I've CoH'd idiots who fall off cliffs or down into pits, which I personally think they deserve to lose exp over.  On average, I probably use CoH 1 time for every 4 raid hours.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  So.....</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br><br>I decided, that regarding <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   MY PESONAL </i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> play style, that I was ripping myself off some serious mana potential by staying a conjuration specialist.  Once grouped, the only time I use conjuration is when things go badly.  On the other hand, I am trying to be as effecient to the group as possible, which means I am malosi'ing and casting Sirroco as often as mana and aggro permits.<br><br>3 Days ago I made the lonely trek to the Temple of Sol Ro with a ruby and 50p.  After an hour of selling crap in EC and chain-casting our level 1 Burst of Flame on myself, I got my specialization evocation up to 112 - I haven't been online since due to the horrible patching in progress.<br><br>That's not to say that I won't change my specialization back to Conjuration when I max out my exp bar at 60 and do nothing but raids...raids on mobs that mages can't cast on and pets are negligable at best.  But, for the time being, I've decided that evocation is the most effeciant form of specialization for what I do, and how I play.<br><br>I would suggest anybody who is considering changing their spec to do something similiar to what I did.  Actually do some logging, take some notes, see where the majority of your mana goes.  If you are a raid fanatic, you are probably an excellent conjurer candidate.  If you are a exp hound (like me), you probably would make a good evoker.<br><br>Hope this helps-<br><br>-Anthe of Luclin<br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uanthe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Anthe</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.facelink.com/AnthetheMage" BORDER=0> at: 11/8/01 12:40:36 pm<br></i></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
